<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 24 at 9:57AM CST  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Benton,
northwestern Madison, northern Carroll and northeastern Washington
Counties through 1030 AM CST...
At 957 AM CST, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
southeast of Hobbs State Park, moving northeast at 75 mph. Very
heavy sleet and freezing rain is also occurring with this storm.
Watch for slick spots that may rapidly develop.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Berryville...                     Eureka Springs...
Green Forest...                   Hindsville...
War Eagle...                      Urbanette...
Hobbs State Park...               Grandview...
Clifty...                         Forum...
Blue Eye...                       Rockhouse...
Pleasant Ridge...                 Denver...
Best...                           Lookout...
Cabanal...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
